<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-084-043 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 214 787</DOCID><JOURNAL>Software Industry Bulletin  August 12 1991 v7 n29 p5(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT DIGital Information Group 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Aldus reports 31% profit gain.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Aldus Corp. (Finance).andO;Ticker:    ALDC.andO;Topic:     Second QuarterFinancial ReportProfitSalesIncreaseFinancial Analysis.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Aldus financial summary. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Aldus Corp. reported record sales for the second calendar quarter as earningsjumped 31% compared with the same quarter a year ago.andP;  A key publisher ofdesktop publishing and graphics software, Aldus reported a $7.61 millionprofit for the second quarter on sales of $44.3 million.andP;  Sales jumped 33%compared with a year ago.andM;Aldus' PageMaker remains its most important product.andP;  The company isgradually reducing its dependence on PageMaker, from 100% of sales in 1985 to66% of sales in 1990.andP;  Aldus expects the figure to drop to 50% next year.andM;Aldus cited strong new unit and upgrade sales of PageMaker 4.0 for Windowsand the release of Aldus Persuasion 2.0 for Windows for its strong financialperformance.andP;  Fifty percent of Aldus' second quarter sales came from outsidethe U.S., up from 40% a year ago.andM;Strong Balance SheetandM;With $91.6 million in cash and marketable securities as of June 30 and nolong-term debt, Aldus' balance sheet is strong.andP;  The company's current ratio(current assets divided by current liabilities) was a very healthy 5.6 to 1at the end of the second quarter.andM;Aldus' market value at the end of trading last week was $576.2 million, 4.2times its book value of $135.7 million.andP;  Aldus' market-to-book ratio is highcompared with most other business software companies.andP;  The company'sprice/earnings ratio was 20.andM;20% Discount Offered on Key ProductsandM;Aldus introduced a relatively novel pricing scheme last week that givesregistered users of PageMaker, Persuasion, and Freehand a 20% discount on asecond copy without disks or documentation.andP;  The License Packs give the buyerthe right to make one copy of the original disks for use on a separatecomputer.andP;  The License Packs give the buyer the right to buy a manual for $95plus tax.andP;  Suggested price for the PageMaker License Pack is $635; $475 forFreehand and $395 for Persuasion.andP;  The License Packs are sold only throughauthorized Aldus resellers.andP;  Manuals are sold directly by Aldus.andO;</TEXT></DOC>